David Rylance was jailed for two years and three months for theft and fraud involving £52,000 . 
  His mother Margaret was suffering from Alzheimer's and was dying of the disease . 
  Pensioner spent money on gambling, a holiday and cinema tickets . 
  Her concerns were put down to her having Alzheimer's disease . 
  Her son had been slowly siphoning the money away from her bank account . 
  Newcastle Crown Court heard one of her accounts held just £1,000 at the time of her death in 2013 . 
 